	     <form action=/cgi-bin/mrate.pl name=f104965891519085>
	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=/search.shtml?id=3239&mid=104965891519085>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=/search.shtml?id=3239&mid=104965891519085>Location</a> <a id=fs8 href=/search.shtml?id=3239&mid=104965891519085#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Sun, Apr 6th 4:01 PM 2003</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=118064><span id=Scholar>mlewin</span></a><br><b><span id=Scholar>Scholar</span></b><br><span id=notbold>37 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>I just got this for my 34th level wizard last night.&nbsp;&nbsp;It was the last piece I needed for the quest, so I was ecstatic when I got it. <br><br>What I found mildly frustrating for this part of the quest was the variance in the information about the location of the Inferno Goblin Wizard. My suspicion is that you can find him as a random pop in either &quot;The Bar&quot; or &quot;Room with Kindle&quot; (numbers 15 and 2, respectively on the EQAtlas map). <br><br>However, I was convinced by somebody in-zone that he found him over and over in a room close to, but not in &quot;The Bar.&quot; To find the room I am talking about, head through the zone as if you are going to &quot;The Bar.&quot; At the four-way intersection just before you reach &quot;The Bar&quot; area, turn right. In front of you should be some stairs going up to a door. The room with the Inferno Goblin Wizard is just beyond that door. We found him and killed him, and he dropped the heart. Be very careful, though, as he has a lot of friends in there that hit extremely hard. <br><br>I would estimate the /loc of the room to be about (neg)775, (neg)610. <br><br>Other tips are to watch for the Inferno Goblin Wizard casting spells even when you can see him. That is ultimately how we located him. Also, that guy in-zone said that we could find the Inferno Goblin Wizard near a shaman. That also turned out to be correct, so if you are in the area, and you see a shaman (not sure if it is Fire or Inferno) then you are probably close. <br><br>I hope this helps some people avoid the hours long camps that seem to plague this part of the quest. <br><br>Slaren, devotee of Solusek Ro <br>Tholuxe Paells server <br></p>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
